## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date empirical studies and the potential bias in personal accounts and opinion pieces. Additionally, the effectiveness of homeschooling can vary significantly depending on the parents' educational background and resources available, which may not be adequately captured in broad statistical analyses. Further research could explore long-term outcomes of homeschooled students in terms of career success and social integration.